question.text: Which of the following statement is not correct?

options.text: <math><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><msub><mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> and <math><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><msub><mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub><mo>]</mo></math> have the same magnetic moment

<math><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> and <math><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> have different shapes

Hybridisation state of Co in <math><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">x</mi><msub><mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><msup><mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></math> is <math><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>

In brown-ring complex <math><mo>[</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mo>(</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><msub><mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi><mo>]</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">S</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></math> oxidation state of Fe is +1

solution.text:
[Co(Ox)3]3-
Co3+=[Ar]4s03d6

[Ni(CN)4]2- and [Ni(CO)4] have zero magnetic moment as have no unpaired electron.
[NiCl4]2- and [PtCl4]2- have different shapes that is tetrahedral and square planar respectively.
In brown-ring complex [Fe(H2O)5NO]SO4 oxidation state of Fe is +1 as NO is taken as +1 here.
